Some things take time. I first saw this bike in easy riders in 92. I was able to see it in person around 93.  Since then I wanted it.  For 25 years I tried. The lord works in mysterious ways. On Christmas Eve, I learned that soon my dream would come true. For myself this is one of the most iconic and influential choppers. Only now do I realize how much my styling reflects Luo Falcigno’s of C&L hog shop. I am grateful to have my turn with this machine. Enjoy the pics. Soon I will have it detailed and running in all its glory with the original S&S L model  that was on this bike. (my brother just happens to have it). Enjoy the pics and stay tuned for more. #Myfirstcar #1965mustang #V8 I bought it when I was 14 for $200 from Kenny Woodruff’s driveway. I saw it one day while riding my Bmx bike. I went home and got the money, I had hustled from cutting yards for $7 and buying and selling bicycles, mini bikes and go karts. $200 back then was like a thousand now. You had to work for it. I used to come home from junior high school (before my parents came home) and drive it around the block with just enough brakes that … if you planned it, you could stop at the stop sign!  I still live in the same house with the lake in the back. It looks a lot different now.

After revising the oil return path, I assembled motor and finished the Hoodride a couple of  days ago. We had unusual rainy weather in Miami. Today the sun shines. The Hoodride. I first built this bike in 1996. Have bought it back 5 or 6 times. Each time doing some revisions using my improved skills, tools and ideas. This is the final job. Features include; 1957 HD frame widened with a portapower and a torch. 16x6” Original Choppers Inc wheel that we made from an e350 van rim. @coopersmithingco custom made to fit rear fender. Aircraft taillight using my custom made stainless body. @sscycle 86” sidewinder. #strociek billet aluminum cylinders. #patkennedy rocker boxes. @fnacustomcycles MAGNETO. @exilecycles rear brake @famousfabricator stainless steel kickstand.  2” stainless pipes by ME. Foot controls by me. A NEW PRODUCT I OFFER IS Handlebars by me. HD springer. Disc brake on a Star hub 23” stainless rim, by ME. @performancemachine front disc brake adapted to a 46 knuckle star hub.  #ART hydraulic kicker cover by @riveraprimoinc. #Delkron oil pump. HD 6V oil tank. Modified to fit @techcycleperformance electric start and use @antigravitybatteries 400 CCA lithium battery. Lower pushrod covers by @exotic_choppers @harleydavidson 80s special edition Marchal headlamp with bar and shield. Carbon fiber headlight shell. And more! @mos_image_customs did the Hotwheels style hot rod flames. @red_racing_hd rebuilt the engine for me. Tommy always does an outstanding job. Fast Freddy will be representing soon!
